<span id="freeTextContainer5888184101353221030">3.5/5 stars -- rounded up because I&apos;m feeling generous.This isn&apos;t Tommy P at his best, but it is Tommy P at his most accessible. <br/><br/>&apos;Inherent Vice&apos; is good for a laugh, but sorta like that last time I smoked pot, I doubt I&apos;ll remember much about it tomorrow. It was a fun experience -- I giggled, I zoned out, got a little paranoid... hey, I think I might have even gotten a case of the munchies. Yeah, man. I sat on my sofa, ate a bag of Doritos, a pint of ice cream, a box of cookies and 6 slices of p</span>
  <span id="freeText5888184101353221030" style="display:none">3.5/5 stars -- rounded up because I'm feeling generous.This isn't Tommy P at his best, but it is Tommy P at his most accessible. <br><br>'Inherent Vice' is good for a laugh, but sorta like that last time I smoked pot, I doubt I'll remember much about it tomorrow. It was a fun experience -- I giggled, I zoned out, got a little paranoid... hey, I think I might have even gotten a case of the munchies. Yeah, man. I sat on my sofa, ate a bag of Doritos, a pint of ice cream, a box of cookies and 6 slices of pizza. Then I fell asleep watching reruns of Gilligan's Island. <br><br>I might have enjoyed the book more if it wasn't for, you know...<br><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380378433i/734061.jpg" width="240" height="210" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br></span>
